   "description":"Elisabet Margareta Emelie Borgström was a pharmacist from Karlskrona, Sweden. She was born on April 22, 1890 in Ljusdal, Gävleborgs län, Sweden, to Major Jakob Gustaf Widmark and Greta Bech. She completed studies in Östersund in 1909 and obtained a degree as a pharmacist in 1912. Borgström was employed at various pharmacies throughout her career, including Gripen in Nyköping, Hjorten in Östersund, and Smedjebacken. She was also a member of several professional and charitable organizations in Karlskrona, including the pharmacist association, the housewives' association, and the association for the support of Pauvres honteux. She passed away on an unknown date."
